PART 5: THE α₁≥α₂ EXTENSION — AVERAGE CYCLE LENGTH BOUND
======================================================================

  For n=10, need a sharper bound than Cauchy-Schwarz on vertices.
  Alternative: use the EDGE clique structure.

  For each arc u→v, the 3-cycles through this arc form a clique in CG.
  Number of such 3-cycles = |N_out(v) ∩ N_in(u)| = common out-neighbors

  n=5: checking edge-clique structure
    checked 784 tournaments
  n=6: checking edge-clique structure
